Title: IPA/IdM Migration from RHEL 8 to RHEL 9 — Plano DC

Assignee: Haj Suma
Priority: High
Component: Infrastructure / Identity Management

---

Summary:
Migrate IPA/IdM master server from cpeg-ipareplica (RHEL 8, IPA 4.9.13) to pln-ipamaster (RHEL 9.3, IPA 4.12.2, Plano DC) to modernize the IPA infrastructure and consolidate identity management services to the Plano datacenter.

Business Justification:
Centralizing IPA/IdM services in the Plano DC improves reliability and positions us on a supported RHEL 9 platform. The current master (cpeg-ipareplica) is running RHEL 8 which is approaching end of life.

Current State:
- cpeg-ipareplica.ipa.calix.local — RHEL 8, IPA 4.9.13 — currently serving all clients
- pln-ipamaster.ipa.calix.local — RHEL 9.3, IPA 4.12.2, Plano DC — installed, partially validated, temporarily reverted

Work Completed:
- Installed pln-ipamaster as CA replica in existing IPA topology
- Replicated full CA database to pln
- Transferred CA renewal master and CRL generation to pln
- Validated core services — DS, KDC, kadmin, httpd, pki-tomcatd
- UI and CLI authentication validated
- Red Hat support case opened — confirmed clean fresh install is recommended path forward

Decision:
Red Hat recommended a clean fresh install rather than migrating the existing CA database due to the size and age of the CA request database. LDAP-confirmed count: 707,842 completed certificate requests accumulated since 2018. Investigation confirmed all existing certificates are host and service certs that can be automatically reissued upon client re-enrollment. CA data does not need to be preserved.

Next Steps:
1. Prune 707,842 completed certificate requests from cpeg o=ipaca database (prerequisite — reduces pki-tomcatd startup from 30-60 min to seconds)
2. Uninstall current pln-ipamaster (ipa-server-install --uninstall)
3. Apply pre-install checklist on pln — installer.conf timeouts, constants.py patch, pki-tomcatd systemd override, time-skew ldif (required to prevent install hang)
4. Fresh install of pln-ipamaster per RH recommendation
5. Migrate user/group/HBAC/sudo/DNS data only — no CA data
6. Post-install validation — cn=masters entries, certmonger, CA health, replication topology
7. Transfer CA renewal master and CRL generation to pln
8. Re-enroll client machines in batch
9. Update all client sssd.conf to point to pln-ipamaster
10. Update OCP-AI LDAP integration to point to pln-ipamaster
11. Decommission cpeg-ipareplica once pln fully validated

Acceptance Criteria:
- ipactl status all green on pln-ipamaster
- kinit admin and ipa user-find working
- All certmonger certs in MONITORING state
- CA renewal master and CRL generation transferred to pln
- cpeg-ipareplica removed from topology and decommissioned
- OCP-AI LDAP auth validated against pln-ipamaster

